  "prompt": "If I delete someone's conversation (old msgs + new unread message) on WhatsApp without reading it and without opening their chat window, will they receive blue ticks?",
  "response": "On WhatsApp, **blue ticks** indicate that a message has been **read** by the recipient. Whether the sender sees blue ticks depends primarily on whether the message is marked as read on your device. Here's how it works in the scenario you described:\n\n1. **Deleting Without Opening the Chat:**\n   - **If you delete the conversation *without* opening the chat window or viewing the message in any form (including via notifications),** WhatsApp will **not** mark the message as read. In this case, the sender will see **two gray ticks**, indicating that the message was delivered to your device but **not** read.\n   \n2. **Viewing via Notifications:**\n   - **If you have message previews enabled** (i.e., you can see a snippet of the message in your notification panel) **and you view the message preview without opening WhatsApp,** this might **still trigger the read receipt**, depending on your device's operating system and WhatsApp's version. As a result, the sender could see blue ticks.\n   \n3. **Read Receipts Settings:**\n   - **If you have disabled read receipts** in WhatsApp settings, **blue ticks won't appear** even if you read the message. However, keep in mind that disabling read receipts is mutual; you also won't see read receipts from others.\n\n4. **Other Considerations:**\n   - **Media Messages:** Opening media (like photos or videos) from the notification might also count as reading the message, triggering blue ticks.\n   - **Group Chats:** In group chats, blue ticks appear when *all* participants have read the message, or if the sender has specified they want to see read receipts.\n\n**In summary:**\n\n- **To ensure the sender does not receive blue ticks**, avoid opening the chat or viewing message previews in notifications before deleting the conversation.\n- **Be aware** that certain actions, like viewing a notification preview, might still mark the message as read.\n\nIf you delete the chat without opening it or viewing the message, WhatsApp won\u2019t mark it as read, and the sender won\u2019t see blue ticks. However, ensure you don\u2019t inadvertently preview the message (e.g., via notifications), as that could trigger read receipts.",
